snippet.textDisplay:
Side theory: Netflix is creating a Christmas universe aristocracy class, with this series and The Princess Switch, maybe more.
When I was forced to watch these movies, I noticed how well the “knightly order” medals were done(the medals worn on the left side of the chest), some look incredibly close to current orders, such as order of the garter etc. But I couldn’t find any that actually matched, just really close, but the orders Richard is apart of are the same ones Edward is part of.

Basically Netflix has a secret English accent, English speaking, Eastern European aristocracy, which has members in numerous royal families and sovereign monarchs which also somehow survived soviet occupation. I think this is a dangerously under-told story (Given that Aldovia apparently owned Constantinople once, also raises questions about the Turks and so many other questions but is another issue entirely)
